AGREEMENT This SHARED GEN-TIE FACILITIES COMMON OWNERSHIP AGREEMENT (Agreement), effective as of March 27, 2020 (the Effective Date) is entered into by and between LITTLE BEAR SOLAR 3, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (LB3), LITTLE BEAR SOLAR 4, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (LB4), LITTLE BEAR SOLAR 5, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (LB5 and with LB3 and LB4, each individually a Owner and collectively Owners), and Little Bear Holding Company, LLC, as administrative manager (Little Bear Holding). LB3, LB4, LB5 and Little Bear Holding (as Administrative Manager) are sometimes referred to herein collectively as the Parties and individually as a Party. RECITALS A. LB3 is developing, and currently expects to construct, own and operate a solar PV electric generating facility to be located in Fresno County, California, with an interconnection capacity of 20 megawatts (MW) (the LB3 Project). B. LB4 is developing, and currently expects to construct, own and operate a solar PV electric generating facility to be located in Fresno County, California, with an interconnection capacity of up to 50 megawatts (MW) (the LB4 Project). C. LB5 is developing, and currently expects to construct, own and operate a solar PV electric generating facility to be located in Fresno County, California, with an interconnection capacity of up to 50 megawatts (MW) (the LB5 Project). E. In connection with the development and operation of their respective Projects, LB3, LB4 and LB5 intend to own and share the use of the Shared Facilities (as defined below), subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. F. The Shared Facilities will utilize the land rights granted pursuant to the easements and encroachment permit (the Encroachment Permit) listed on Exhibit B-1 (Easements), subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. G. The purpose of this Agreement is to document the agreement of the Parties as to their individual and common ownership rights, obligations, and use with respect to the Shared Facilities. H. The Parties also wish to contract with Administrative Manager for the provision of certain services with respect to the Shared Facilities and the Administrative Manager wishes to accept such engagement. I. The Owners are also parties to the Second Amended and Restated Shared Gen-Tie Facilities Common Ownership Agreement, dated on or about the date hereof, between North Star Solar, LLC, Little Bear Solar 1, LLC, LB3, LB4 and LB5 (the NSS SFA), which governs the ownership and operation of the Shared Gen-Tie Facilities (as defined in the NSS SFA). J. Capitalized terms used in these Recitals that are not otherwise defined in the preamble paragraph of this Agreement have the same meanings ascribed to such terms in Section 1.1 below. 104590859.11 0065403-00009 AGREEMENT NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual agreements set forth herein, the Parties agree as follows: ARTICLE 1 DEFINITIONS 1.1 Certain Definitions. ARTICLE 2 OWNERSHIP AND USE OF SHARED FACILITIES 2.1 Ownership of Shared Facilities. As of the Effective Date, the Owners respective Shared Facilities Ownership Percentages are as follows, subject to the adjustments set forth herein: (i) LB3 holds an undivided sixteen point six percent (16.6%) Shared Facilities Ownership Percentage; (ii) LB4 holds an undivided forty-one -8-
104590859.11 0065403-00009 point seven percent (41.7%) Shared Facilities Ownership Percentage; and (iii) LB5 holds an undivided forty-one point seven percent (41.7%) Shared Facilities Ownership Percentage. (a) Administrative Manager will be solely responsible (without any reimbursement from the Owners) for all initial costs incurred for the design, procurement, construction, and installation of the Shared Facilities. (b) In the event LB3, LB4 and/or LB5 elects not to use the Shared Facilities, it shall have the right to terminate its rights and obligations hereunder by delivering written notice of such termination (a Termination Notice) setting forth the date of such termination (the Termination Date) to the other Owners. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, in the event LB3, LB4 and/or LB5 delivers a Termination Notice, then effective as of the applicable Termination Date, such Person shall have no further rights or obligations hereunder (or hold any ownership interest) to the extent pertaining to the period from and after the applicable Termination Date, and effective as of the applicable Termination Date, any ownership interest held by such termination party shall revert to the other Owners holding any Shared Facilities Ownership Percentage in proportion to the respective Maximum Capacity of such Owners Projects. (c) Statement of Intent. The ownership structure set forth in this Section 2.1 is not organized with the intention or expectation of producing revenue or making a profit from the operation of the Shared Facilities but merely as an ownership form through which the Owners can accomplish their purpose of owning, operating and making the Shared Facilities available for the use of the Owners in connection with their respective, separate Projects. Nothing in this Agreement is intended or shall be construed to create any partnership, joint venture or similar relationship between LB3, LB4 and/or LB5; and in no event shall any Owner take a position on any tax return or other writing of any kind that a partnership, joint venture or other similar relationship exists. The Owners do not intend to form or hold themselves out as a de jure or de facto partnership, joint venture or similar relationship, to share profits or losses, or to share any joint control over financial decisions or discretionary actions (other than as may be expressly provided herein or in the Land Rights Documents). At no time shall the Shared Facilities be used by any person other than an Owner, except as otherwise may be required by Law. Subject to the rights of each Owner under Article 7, in the event of the possible sale or other disposition of its ownership interest in the Shared Facilities, or under Section 12.4 in the event all or a portion of the Shared Facilities is or are removed from service, the Owners do not expect to receive any material amount of revenue from the Shared Facilities. 2.2 Use of Shared Facilities; Outages. (a) The Owners shall cooperate in good faith to use the Shared Facilities in which they hold an ownership interest in accordance with this Agreement to accomplish the interconnection of the Projects so as to minimize, to the extent reasonably practicable, the interruption and reduction of deliveries from the Projects of the other Owners. The Owners and their respective successors and assigns shall use the Shared Facilities in which they hold an ownership interest in compliance with all applicable laws, the Land Rights Documents and this Agreement. The Owners and their respective successors and assigns shall coordinate and cooperate in good faith to facilitate (a) the joint benefit and use of, and access to, the Shared Facilities by the Owners that hold an ownership interest in such Shared Facilities in accordance with this Agreement and (b) the -9-
104590859.11 0065403-00009 effective and cost-efficient operation, maintenance and use of the Shared Facilities by the Owners holding an ownership interest therein, in each case, in a manner consistent with this Agreement. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, each Owner shall provide the other Owners with reasonable access to the Shared Facilities in which such Owners hold an ownership interest so that each Owner and/or its contractors and vendors can perform the obligations under such Owners construction, operation or maintenance agreements pertaining to the Shared Facilities in which such Owner holds an ownership interest. (b) To the extent any Owners Project is disconnected, incurs any downtime, is curtailed or interrupted or experiences an outage, in each case with resulting loss of production and revenue to such Project, and to the extent the loss results from another Owners actions or inactions (including, without limitation, outages, interruptions or disconnections during the construction of an Owners Project), then, in any case, the responsible Owner shall reimburse the other Owner for the applicable Lost Production Damages to the extent resulting therefrom within thirty (30) days after delivery of notice and supporting documentation of the loss. For the avoidance of doubt, an Owner will not be required to pay both Lost Production Damages (as defined in the NSS SFA) under the NSS SFA and Lost Production Damages under this Section 2.2(b) for the same loss of production and revenue to a relevant Project. 2.3 Use of Shared Facilities; Interconnection and Curtailment. (a) Interconnection - Project Maximum Capacity Limitation. LB3, LB4 and LB5 and their respective successors and assigns shall have the right, at their respective sole cost and expense (other than with respect to the costs and liabilities which are to be shared by the Owners as expressly provided herein), to interconnect their Projects at 115 kV and to deliver electrical energy generated by their respective Projects up to their respective Projects Maximum Capacity to the Point of Interconnection via the Shared Facilities; provided, however, that (i) the design of such interconnection shall be in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice and such Owners Interconnection Agreement and such interconnection with the Shared Facilities shall be subject to the reasonable approval of the Administrative Manager (which shall not be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed), (ii) LB3, LB4 and LB5 and their respective successors and assigns shall not use the Shared Facilities to transmit electricity bi-directionally from and to their respective Projects in an amount exceeding each such respective Owners Projects Maximum Capacity, nor at any time interconnect with the Shared Facilities electric generation facilities with an aggregate capacity (net of losses arising prior to the Point of Interconnection) that exceeds each such respective Owners Project's Maximum Capacity, and (iii) LB3, LB4 and LB5 and their respective successors and assigns will be responsible, as specified in the respective Interconnection Agreements, for all initial costs incurred by the Transmission Owner for the design, procurement, construction, and installation of the Participating TOs Interconnection Facilities, as well as all ongoing costs, including operation and maintenance costs, associated with the Participating TOs Interconnection Facilities. (b) Curtailment. LB3, LB4 and LB5 and their respective successors and assigns shall promptly interrupt, reduce or curtail deliveries of energy to or on the Shared Facilities (a) when necessary in order to maintain or repair any part of the Shared Facilities and/or to facilitate the interconnection of any Owners Project using the Shared Facilities, (b) if interruption, reduction or curtailment is necessary for safety or System Emergencies or the energy delivered to, or -10-

The duties, obligations and liabilities of the Owners under this Agreement are intended to be several and not joint or collective, and no Owner shall be jointly and severally liable for the acts, omissions or obligations of any other Owner. Nothing contained in this Agreement shall be construed to create an association, joint venture, or partnership, or impose a partnership duty, obligation or liability, among the Owners. No Owner shall have a right or power to bind any other Owner without its express written consent, except as expressly otherwise provided in this Agreement. 12.3 Governing Law. This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of California. 12.4 Removal of Shared Facilities from Service. When all of the Owners direct the Administrative Manager to permanently remove the Shared Facilities from service or as otherwise required by the Land Rights Documents, and subject to the Owners providing the Administrative Manager with their Share of the funds to complete such work in advance, the Administrative Manager shall as agent for and on behalf of the Owners engage a third party to dispose of (or arrange for disposal of) the Shared Facilities, or of such part of the Shared Facilities, as the case may be, being removed from service. After deducting all costs of disposing of the Shared Facilities, or of such part of the Shared Facilities, as the case may be, including, without limitation, the cost of removing all structures and disposing of the debris and -33-
104590859.11 0065403-00009 meeting all requirements of applicable law, the Administrative Manager shall distribute to each Owner its Share of net proceeds from such disposition. In the event such costs of disposing of the Shared Facilities, or of part of the Shared Facilities, as the case may be, pursuant to this Section 12.4. exceed the amount of the proceeds from the disposition of the Shared Facilities or such part of the Shared Facilities, each Owner shall pay its Share of excess costs related to the disposition of the Shared Facilities or of such part of the Shared Facilities, as the case may be, as such excess costs are incurred. 12.5 Uncontrollable Forces. No Owner shall be considered to be in default under this Agreement or in breach of this Agreement on account of any failure in the performance of any of its obligations under this Agreement, other than obligations of such Owner to make any payments that are due and owing pursuant to this Agreement, if failure of such performance is due to the occurrence of a Force Majeure Event. Force Majeure Event, as used herein, means any act or event that delays or prevents an Owner from timely performing all or a portion of its obligations under this Agreement or from complying with all or a portion of the conditions under this Agreement if such act or event, despite the exercise of reasonable efforts, cannot be avoided by and is beyond the reasonable control of and without the fault or negligence of the Owner relying thereon as justification for such delay, nonperformance, or noncompliance. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, so long as the following events, despite the exercise of reasonable efforts, cannot be avoided by, and are beyond the reasonable control of and without the fault or negligence of the Owner relying thereon as justification for such delay, nonperformance and noncompliance, Force Majeure Events may include without limitation: acts of God; actions of the elements such as heavy rains, floods, earthquakes, hurricanes, tornadoes, the solar impacts of volcanic action, lightning, ice storms, landslides, mudslides, high winds of sufficient strength or duration to materially damage the Shared Facilities or significantly impair their operation for a period of time; subsurface or other site conditions (including, without limitation, environmental contamination, archaeological or other protected cultural resources, and endangered species or protected habitats); explosion; fire; epidemic; sabotage; terrorism; transportation delays; unavailability of materials; defective equipment or equipment failure due to equipment design defects, equipment manufacturing defects or any other cause other than an Owners failure to comply with Prudent Industry Practice; an act of public enemy; war; blockade; civil insurrection; riot; civil disturbance or strike or other labor difficulty caused or suffered by an Owner or any third Person beyond the reasonable control of such Owner or its Affiliates (even if such difficulties could be resolved by conceding to the demands of a labor group); directives from the Transmission Provider causing an Owner or the Administrative Manager to divert output to address reliability concerns or System Emergency; System Emergencies affecting a Project; or any restraint or restriction imposed by applicable law or any directive from a government authority, to the extent that by exercise of due diligence and in compliance with applicable law an Owner could not reasonably have been expected to avoid, and to the extent that by exercise of due diligence and in compliance with applicable law, an Owner has been unable to overcome (so long as the affected Owner has not applied for or assisted such act by a governmental authority). Any Owner or Administrative Manager rendered unable to fulfill any obligation under this Agreement by reason of a Force Majeure Event shall give written notice of such Force Majeure Event promptly to each Owner and the Administrative Manager and shall exercise due diligence to remove such inability with all reasonable dispatch. -34-
104590859.11 0065403-00009 12.6 Run With the Land. Upon the request of an Owner, any other Owner, upon not less than ten (10) business days written notice, shall, if true, provide a written certificate stating that (i) this Agreement is in full force and effect and has not been modified or amended (or if modified or amended, stating so), and (ii) to the actual knowledge of the certifying Owner, there are no defaults under this Agreement and no events that, with notice or the passage of time or both, could become a default (or if there are defaults, describing them in reasonable detail). The requesting Owner, and any purchaser, investor or lender with respect to such Owners portion of the Shared Facilities, shall be entitled to rely on the truthfulness of the statements made by the certifying Owner in such certificate. The failure of the non-requesting Owner to deliver any such certificate within such time shall be conclusive upon such non-requesting Owner that (i) this Agreement and the rights granted hereunder are in full force and effect and have not been modified and (ii) there are no uncured defaults hereunder. 12.8 Partition Waiver. The Owners agree that the Shared Facilities are not suitable for partition. Accordingly, each Owner irrevocably waives any and all rights that it may have under applicable law to maintain any action, suit or claim for partition of all or any part of the Shared Facilities. In the event that any Owner is an entity that distributes its interest in the Shared Facilities and this Agreement to its members, shareholders, partners or owners voluntarily, in the course of dissolution or by operation of law, such distribution shall comply with all requirements of Article 7 of this Agreement, the distributees shall become Owners under this Agreement and each distributee shall be bound by the terms of this Agreement, including the waiver of any partition rights. 12.9 Term. The Term of the Agreement commenced on the Effective Date and continues in effect for so long as any of the Land Rights Documents remain in effect, plus any time required for disposing of such Shared Facilities as provided in Section 12.4 of the Agreement, unless terminated earlier by mutual agreement of the Owners. -35-
